roper motion measurement of the source. The\nplanet may be orbiting a star but we rule out the presence of stellar\ncompanions up to the projected distance of 8.0 au from the planet. Our\ndiscovery demonstrates that terrestrial-mass free-floating planets can be\ndetected and characterized using microlensing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Sep 2020 18:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 20 Oct 2020 07:38:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-11"}
