{"id":"2009.12440","submitter":"Wesley Perkins","authors":"Mathew A. Johnson, Wesley R. Perkins","title":"Subharmonic Dynamics of Wave Trains in Reaction Diffusion Systems","comments":"24 pages. Updated exposition and incorporated referee comments","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.physd.2021.132891","report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We investigate the stability and nonlinear local dynamics of spectrally\nstable wave trains in reaction-diffusion systems. For each $N\\in\\mathbb{N}$,\nsuch $T$-periodic traveling waves are easily seen to be nonlinearly\nasymptotically stable (with asymptotic phase) with exponential rates of decay\nwhen subject to $NT$-periodic, i.e., subharmonic, perturbations. However, both\nthe allowable size of perturbations and the exponential rates of decay depend\non $N$, and, in particular, they tend to zero as $N\\to\\infty$, leading to a\nlack of uniformity in such subharmonic stability results. In this work, we\nbuild on recent work by the authors and introduce a methodology that allows us\nto achieve a stability result for subharmonic perturbations which is uniform in\n$N$. Our work is motivated by the dynamics of such waves when subject to\nperturbations which are localized (i.e. integrable on the line), which has\nrecently received considerable attention by many authors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Sep 2020 21:26:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Mar 2021 18:18:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-28"}
